S.Korean soldier shot dead near border with DPRK
2013-03-18 03:35:45 GMT
By Mei Jingya, Sina EnglishA S.Korean soldier serving on the front line was shot dead in near the border with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), Seoul's Joongang Ilbo reported Monday.S.Korean military has launched an investigation into the death.The newspaper quoted an army source as saying a gunshot was heard around 2 pm, Sunday in Gangwon-do Cheorwon-gun.Fellow troops recalled the dead, surnamed Kim, said he need to go to the bathroom. He was found dead with gunshot wounds a moment later.
